posts.title: the usage of git
posts.text: generally ,we always using the commond :git remote origin ;to bind this remote repo to the name:origin .if we pull or push we can using origin rather than the url or ssh..when you change the file in your working zone,you must add and commit .then push to the remote repo.if you want to rollback this add or remove,you can use the commond git reset HEAD filename;and if you want to checkout the branch but there are change in add zone,you need to stash the change,then you can checkout to other branch,when you return to the first branch ,you can use the commond :git stash pop .
